claim.claim-text:
A multi-stage amplifier (200) comprising
- a first amplification stage (260, 261) configured to activate or to deactivate a first output stage (270, 271, 201) in response to an input voltage at an input node (255);
- the first output stage (270, 271, 201) configured to source a current at an output node (301) of the multi-stage amplifier (200) from a high potential (302), when activated;
- a second amplification stage (400, 401) configured to activate or to deactivate a second output stage (410, 411, 412) in response to the input voltage at the input node (255); and
- the second output stage (410, 411, 412) configured to sink a current at the output node (301) of the multi-stage amplifier (200) to a low potential (303), when activated; wherein the first amplification stage (260, 261) and the second amplification stage (400, 401) are configured to activate the first output stage (270, 271, 201) and the second output stage (410, 411, 412) in a mutually exclusive manner.

The multi-stage amplifier (200) of any of claims 2 to 5, wherein
- the first input transistor (260) comprises a first partial transistor (460) and a second partial transistor (461);
- the first partial transistor (460) and the second partial transistor (461) are arranged in series;
- a gate of the first partial transistor (460) and a gate of the second partial transistor (461) are coupled to the input node (255); and
- a source of the second input transistor (430) is coupled to a midpoint between the first partial transistor (460) and the second partial transistor (461).

The multi-stage amplifier (200) of any of claims 7 to 8, wherein
- the first output amplifier (271, 201) comprises a first current mirror with a first diode transistor (271) and a first output transistor (201);
- the first diode transistor (271) is arranged in series with the first control transistor (270) such that the first diode transistor (271) is traversed by the first control current;
- a drain of the first output transistor (201) is coupled to the output node (301);
- the first output transistor (201) is traversed by the amplified version of the first control current, which is sourced at the output node (301);
- the second output amplifier (411, 412) comprises a second current mirror with a second diode transistor (411) and a second output transistor (412);
- the second diode transistor (411) is arranged in series with the second control transistor (410) such that the second diode transistor (411) is traversed by the second control current;
- a drain of the second output transistor (412) is coupled to the output node (301); and
- the second output transistor (412) is traversed by the amplified version of the second control current, which is sunk at the output node (301).

The multi-stage amplifier (200) of claim 9, wherein
- the first output transistor (201) and the second output transistor (412) are arranged in series;
- the output node (301) corresponds to a midpoint between the first output transistor (201) and the second output transistor (412);
- a source of the first output transistor (201) is coupled to the high potential (302);
- a source of the second output transistor (412) is coupled to the low potential (303);
- a source of the first diode transistor (271) is coupled to the high potential (302);
- a source of the first control transistor (270) is coupled to the low potential (303);
- a source of the second diode transistor (411) is coupled to the low potential (303); and
- a source of the second control transistor (410) is coupled to the high potential (302).

The multi-stage amplifier (200) of any of claims 7 to 10, wherein
- the first control transistor (270) comprises an N-type metaloxide semiconductor, referred to as MOS, transistor;
- the first output amplifier (271, 201) comprises P-type MOS transistors;
- the second control transistor (410) comprises a P-type MOS transistor; and
- the second output amplifier (411, 412) comprises N-type MOS transistors.

A method (600) for stabilizing an output voltage at an output node (301) of a multi-stage amplifier (200), the method (600) comprising
- activating or deactivating (601) a first output stage (270, 271, 201) in response to an input voltage at an input node (255) using a first amplification stage (260, 261); wherein the input voltage at the input node (255) is dependent on the output voltage at the output node (301);
- activating or deactivating (602) a second output stage (410, 411, 412) in response to the input voltage at the input node (255) using a second amplification stage (400, 401); wherein the first amplification stage (260, 261) and the second amplification stage (400, 401) are configured to activate the first output stage (270, 271, 201) and the second output stage (410, 411, 412) in a mutually exclusive manner;
- sourcing (603) a current at the output node (301) of the multi-stage amplifier (200) from a high potential (302), by activating the first output stage (270, 271, 201), if the input voltage at the input node (255) is indicative of an undervoltage situation at the output node (301); and
- sinking (604) a current at the output node (301) of the multi-stage amplifier (200) to a low potential (303), by activating the second output stage (410, 411, 412), if the input voltage at the input node (255) is indicative of an overvoltage situation at the output node (301).
